  "issue_title": "BUG: file fetches for PRs only returning up to 30 files",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nper Taooutsider in #274 \n> GitHub returns only 30 files by default for PR file listings. For PRs with many changed files, scoring could miss file diffs and undercount contribution value.\n\nHis solution had conflicts and he became unresponsive, so I closed his PR and raise this issue in hopes to get a clean PR with a responsive submitter since he brought up a genuine bug.\n\nThe issue is clear, fix  the file fetching so that we can pull ALL files for a PR diff instead of just 30. Please use pagination or whatever is most optimal for conserving API requests. Please provide the computation for how many more API requests this uses in comparison to what currently exists in the code.\n\n## Additional Context\n\nexample PR which only 30 files were scored but has 44 changed files:\n\n<img width=\"1468\" height=\"771\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/394e1181-2525-40f0-b528-9f2e69009e82\" />\n\n",
